    "extract_units_prompt = \"\"\"\n",
    "You are an expert document parser. Your sole task is to extract only **individually priced line items** from the **item description tables** found in this document. Do not include any lot-based entries, group-subtotaled items, or placeholders without individual prices.\n",
    "\n",
    "Your output must be a structured representation that precisely reflects the source data and adheres to the provided Pydantic schema without assumptions or alterations.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**General Extraction Rules**\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Strict Column Separation**:\n",
    "   - Treat the following as **distinct columns** even if they appear combined in the source:\n",
    "     - `Price` (line item price)\n",
    "     - `UQ` or `U/M` (Unit of Measure or Unit Quantity)\n",
    "     - `Unit Quantity` or similar terms (e.g., \"Number of Units\")\n",
    "   - These columns must not be merged or inferred from each other. Pay extra attention to distinguish between `Price` and `UQ`.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Preserve Original Headers**:\n",
    "   - Retain the **exact spelling, casing, and phrasing** of the column headers.\n",
    "   - Do not change, abbreviate, or normalize headers in any way.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **Include All Columns**:\n",
    "   - Extract **every visible column** from the item description table(s).\n",
    "   - If a cell is blank, include the column and use `null` or an empty string in that row — never drop the column.\n",
    "\n",
    "4. **Multi-Page Tables**:\n",
    "   - Table headers may appear only on the **first page**. Assume they apply to subsequent pages unless redefined.\n",
    "\n",
    "5. **Schema Compliance**:\n",
    "   - You must follow the provided Pydantic schema exactly.\n",
    "   - Do not add, remove, infer, or reformat any fields.\n",
    "\n",
    "6. **Handle \"Included\" Pricing**:\n",
    "   - If a line item has `\"included\"` in the `Price` or `ExtPrice` column (e.g., `(included)`), treat it as a valid item.\n",
    "   - Retain `\"included\"` as the value for `Price` and `ExtPrice` (do not replace it with a number or `null`).\n",
    "   - Do not exclude these rows — they are considered individual items even if not priced numerically.\n",
    "   - Items labeled with “included” should still be extracted, as they are part of the structured table and carry item-level metadata (e.g., Qty, MFG, Part). Do not exclude these.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**How to Identify Individual Items**\n",
    "\n",
    "Only extract rows that meet **Most** of the following criteria:\n",
    "\n",
    "- The row contains a **non-null price** OR has the word `included` (e.g., \"(included)\") in the price field\n",
    "- Has values for at least some of:\n",
    "  - `MFG` (Manufacturer)\n",
    "  - `Part` (Part number or ID)\n",
    "  - `Type` (Item category)\n",
    "  - `Quantity`\n",
    "- May have `U/M` listed as `E` (each) or `UoM` as `EA`\n",
    "\n",
    "Each row that meets these conditions is considered a distinct, billable line item and should be included.\n",
    "**Exclude rows only if they are clearly part of a lot, subtotal group, or have no pricing **and no reference to \"included\"**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**DO NOT**:\n",
    "- Include any lots ((\"LOT\" word explicitly mentioned in part/ description) or group-subtotaled rows\n",
    "- Include items with `U/M` = `LT` \n",
    "- Normalize headers or values\n",
    "- Make assumptions or merge multiple rows\n",
    "- Add values not explicitly visible in the document\n",
    "\n",
    "Your only goal is precise, structure-preserving extraction of **individual items with a defined price**.\n",
    "\"\"\"\n"
   ]
