   "source": [
    "\n",
    "summary_prompt = \"\"\"\n",
    "You are a summarization assistant helping to analyze structured data extracted from a document.\n",
    "\n",
    "The data includes rows that may represent **line items** or **lots**. Use the following rules to classify them:\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**Rules for identifying LINE ITEMS:**\n",
    "A row is a *line item* if it meets ALL of the following:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. It has either:\n",
    "   - A **non-null price**, OR\n",
    "   - Contains the word `\"included\"` (case-insensitive) in 'Price' field\n",
    "\n",
    "2. AND typically includes \"most or all\" of the following fields:\n",
    "   - `MFG` (Manufacturer)\n",
    "   - `Part` (Part number or ID)\n",
    "   - `Type` (Item category)\n",
    "   - `Quantity`\n",
    "\n",
    "3. AND the `Part` field **does not start with** `\"LOT\"` (case-insensitive)\n",
    "\n",
    "Optionally, `U/M` may be `\"E\"` or `\"EA\"`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Each such row is counted as a distinct **billable line item**, even if it is a duplicate of another.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**Rules for identifying LOTS:**\n",
    "\n",
    "A row (or group of rows) is considered a *lot* if any of the following conditions are met:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. A block of consecutive rows with no individual pricing (i.e., `Price`, `UQ`, and `ExtPrice` are blank or null), and later followed by a subtotal line like `\"Total for: <LOT_NAME> $<amount>\"` or `\"Subtotal for: <LOT_NAME> $<amount>\"` (These rows may span multiple pages), These rows may include or omit `Qty`, `Type`, `MFG`, and `Part` fields.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. A **single line entry** is also considered a lot if:\n",
    "   - The `U/M` field is `\"LT\"` (lot), OR\n",
    "   - The `Part` field **starts with** `\"LOT\"` (case-insensitive)\n",
    "\n",
    "> These `\"LOT...\"` `Part` values must be **included in the lot count** and listed in `lot_names` — even if no subtotal line appears.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Each such block is considered a **distinct lot**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Your Tasks:\n",
    "Based on the JSON provided:\n",
    "\n",
    "{\n",
    "  \"lots_detected\": Boolean, // boolean value indication whether there are any Lot's in the document//\n",
    "\n",
    "  \"num_lots\": int, // count of total number of lots including those where the `Part` value starts with `\"LOT\"` in the document//\n",
    "\n",
    "  \"lot_names\": [string], // list of lot names (including those `\"LOT...\"` `Part` values as-is (e.g., `\"LOT 1234\"`), if available//\n",
    "\n",
    "  \"items_detected\": Boolean, //boolean value indication whether there are any line item's in the document//\n",
    "\n",
    "  \"num_items\": int,  \n",
    "  // count of total number of items including duplicates part numbers in the document \n",
    "  // Do NOT count any row as a line item if the Part field starts with \"LOT\" (case-insensitive). These are treated as lot and should be excluded from num_items & item_names.\n",
    "  // Do Not count any row as a line item if it has no price. These are treated as lot and should be excluded from num_items & item_names.\n",
    "\n",
    "  \"item_names\": [string], \n",
    "  //full list of part/item names **including duplicates**-- if available\n",
    "  //(Always include duplicates when counting line items and listing their names)\n",
    "\n",
    "  \"consistency_check\": Boolean,\n",
    "  // `true` if the value of `num_items` matches the length of `item_names` & `num_lots` matches the length of `lot_names`, `false` otherwise (If `false`, explain why in `issues`)\n",
    "  //Ensure that the number of item names listed in `item_names` matches the exact count given in `num_items` and `num_lots` matches the length of `lot_names`\n",
    "\n",
    "  \"issues\": [string] // list of structural issues (e.g., missing fields, duplicate names, subtotal not found)//\n",
    "\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "### For Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "```json\n",
    "{\n",
    "  \"lots_detected\": true,\n",
    "  \"num_lots\": 3,\n",
    "  \"lot_names\": [\"CONTROLS\", \"LOT SPARES PER 260505\", \"Lot 25\"], //count of lot names matches the num_lots\n",
    "  \"items_detected\": true,\n",
    "  \"num_items\": 3,\n",
    "  \"item_names\": [\"UBG-F-5-HS304-L240-1C-A-UN-TM\", \"E3RFB-HW\", \"APPROX 24FT RUN C/O\"], //count of item names matches the num_items\n",
    "  \"consistency_check\": True\n",
    "  \"issues\": [\n",
    "    \"One lot has no subtotal line\",\n",
    "    \"Duplicate item Part B456 found twice\"\n",
    "  ]\n",
    "}\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "deployment = \"gpt-4.1\"\n",
    "\n",
    "client = AzureOpenAI(\n",
    "    api_version=\"2024-12-01-preview\",\n",
    "    azure_endpoint=\"https://idpusdwkshpaif7502482903.openai.azure.com/\",\n",
    "    api_key=\""\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "response = client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "    messages=[\n",
    "        {\n",
    "            \"role\": \"system\",\n",
    "            \"content\": summary_prompt\n",
    "        },\n",
    "        {\n",
    "            \"role\": \"user\",\n",
    "            \"content\": user_message_content\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    max_tokens=4096,\n",
    "    temperature=1.0,\n",
    "    top_p=1.0,\n",
    "    model=deployment\n",
    "    \n",
    ")\n",
    "response_text = response.choices[0].message.content\n",
    "print(response.choices[0].message.content)"
   ]
